But the quality and perfomance are identical.The scope is a Bushnell Elite 3200 4-12x40 AO (adjustable objective), with lens covers.For those not familiar, the Elites are not the inexpensive Wal-mart Bushnells (which still generally run fine), the Elite series is their premium line, like Lexus is to Toyota. Years ago, Bushnell bought out the very respected Bausch & Lomb of Japan, but continued production under the Elite name, and all the Elite series has been widely known as top quality optics, and have a lifetime manufacturer's guarantee. Unlike most rifle sales here, there is ZERO need to upgrade this scope.The scope rings are a set of steel Warnes, a top quality scope ring (and I still have the factory ring set).Also included is the sling, case, and 4 boxes (80 rounds) of Federal Gold Medal Match Grade Sierra BTHP (boat-tailed hollow points), which are as high quality a round as you can buy,anywhere.(this is an easy $100 worth of premium ammo).Buyer must be legal to own firearms, and be a legal Ga resident, with valid ID. title: For Sale:  Leupold Mark AR 1.5-4x20
postcontent: This is a Leupold 1.5-4x20mm Mark AR scope. It has the duplex reticle. This is a perfect low power variable for an AR. It has exposed, zero resettable turrets. The elevation turret is calibrated for 55 grain .223 an has quick reference hold over markings out to 650 yards if zeroed at 100 yards. Very simple and effective. Turrets have nice positive clicks. This is a great optic for your rifle that will get you some extra magnification for those longer shots. This would also work great for a lightweight .223 bolt action rifle for hunting coyote or hogs. Great clear glass. Some people will tell you that you can't shoot the 1.5 mag with both eyes open. I disagree, at short ranges up to about 50 yards it is no probem, then dial up the mag and close an eye for the longer shots. It isn't the same as a true 1 power yes... but much cheaper, and definitely works once you get used to it. This is a great scope, I'm almost sad to let it go. No it does not come with a mount or rings. This is $299 brand new on optics planet.
